# Scripts Conventions

- All project scripts belong under `scripts/`.
- Follow the folder structure in [docs/design-principles/architecture.md](docs/design-principles/architecture.md): `setup/`, `migrations/`, `deploy/`, `generate/`, `ingest/`, `verify/`, `dev/`, and optionally `lib/` for shared helpers.
- One script per concern; document purpose, env vars, and usage in a header comment.
- Use TypeScript for logic that uses app types or Neo4j; use shell for simple setup/deploy.
- When adding a new script, place it in the correct subdirectory; do not add scripts at repo root or under `src/`.
